  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 11 high, 9 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD); plus 9 other bases. 9 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK). Network hotspots: Turku (TKU/EFTU), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: low cloud base, fog / freezing fog and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Almaty (ALA/UAAA) and 9 others.",
